Thus, with the aid of the extensive data available, the statistic population was sufficient to produce the diagram shown in Fig. 6
                        , which shows the THR of LFP cells as a function of their SOC and the type of calorimeter used for the measurement. It clearly shows that the higher the SOC of the cell, the higher the heat release. This tendency is opposite to the HF gas emission from LFP cells, where with increase of the SOC the amount of HF gas emitted decreases (see Fig. 7
                        ).
